1 (E) Arkansas Fallen Firefighters Memorial Board under §
2 22-3-1704; and
3 (F) Hoxie: The First Stand Memorial Monument Fund.
4
5 SECTION 3. Arkansas Code Title 19, Chapter 5, Subchapter 11, is
6 amended to add an additional section to read as follows:
7 19-5-1160. Hoxie: The First Stand Memorial Monument Fund.
8 (a) There is established on the books of the Treasurer of State, the
9 Auditor of State, and the Chief Fiscal Officer of the State a trust fund to
10 be known as the “Hoxie: The First Stand Memorial Monument Fund”.
11 (b) The fund shall consist of gifts, grants, and donations from
12 individuals and organizations as provided under the Hoxie: The First Stand
13 Memorial Monument Act, § 22-3-224, and other funds as may be provided by law.
14 (c) The fund shall be used exclusively for the purpose of erecting and
15 maintaining a suitable monument on the State Capitol grounds in recognition
16 and appreciation of the integration of Hoxie public schools in 1955, as
17 provided in the Hoxie: The First Stand Memorial Monument Act, § 22-3-224.
18
19 SECTION 4. Arkansas Code Title 22, Chapter 3, Subchapter 2, is amended
20 to add an additional section to read as follows:
21 22-3-224. Hoxie: The First Stand Memorial Monument Act.
22 (a) This section shall be known and may be cited as the “Hoxie: The
23 First Stand Memorial Monument Act”.
24 (b)(1) The Secretary of State shall permit and arrange for the
25 placement on the State Capitol grounds of a monument commemorating the
26 integration of Hoxie public schools in 1955.
27 (2) The monument shall be placed on the State Capitol grounds
28 where there are other monuments.
29 (3)(A) The monument shall be designed and constructed in the
30 manner recommended by Hoxie the First Stand Inc., or in a manner similar to
31 the design recommended by Hoxie the First Stand Inc.
32 (B) The Secretary of State shall approve the design and
33 site selection for the monument through consultation with the Capitol Arts
34 and Grounds Commission.
35 (c) The Secretary of State may accept gifts, grants, and donations
36 from individuals and organizations to be deposited as trust funds into the
